g.text: Marijuana arrests decline as legislation gains steam
Possession arrests by age and sex
With the legalization of medical marijuana in 2018, Black and white Missouri residents were arrested less than they were in 2010. All races saw a hike in arrests in 2016 and 2017.
Marijuana possession arrests decline following medical legalization in Missouri

Possession arrests across the U.S.

In the United States, Wyoming and South Dakota had the highest rate of marijuana arrests in 2019 â€” both at more than 400 arrests per 100,000 people in the state. Missouri had a rate of 221 arrests per 100,000
ANNIE JENNEMANN/Missourian
How much pot is a crime in Missouri?

Medical marijuana was legalized in Missouri in 2018. Now some legislators are trying to legalize recreational marijuana in 2022. In the meantime, people continue to be arrested for possessing marijuana.Who exactly is being arrested?
American Indian and Alaska Native residents have stayed below 1.5 arrests per 100,000 over time
Asian and Native Hawaiian residents have stayed below one arrest per 100,000 over time
Possession of up to 10 grams:Misdemeanor

In 2014, HB 2238 was passed in Missouri, which allowed for the creation of cannabidiol oil care centers and cultivation and production facilities. It legalized hemp extracts that were equal or less than .3% THC, the active ingredient in marijuana responsible for most of its psychological effects, and at least 5% CBD by weight.
